OL,7,FJoseph Rogan relies on machines 24
OL,8,Fhours a day, seven days a week to help
OL,9,Fhim breathe. He fears Britain's
OL,10,Fspiralling energy costs means he will
OL,11,Fno longer be able to afford the price
OL,12,Fof the life-saving support.
OL,14,FThe father-of-one, who suffers with
OL,15,Fend-stage chronic obstructive pulmonary
OL,16,Fdisease (COPD), is paying British Gas
OL,17,Fmore than #400 a month for his energy
OL,18,Fbill. It is more than double what it
OL,19,Fcost him last year.
OL,3,C'I'm hooked to machines 24/7 to keep me
OL,4,Cbreathing - I could die if my #400
OL,5,Cenergy bill rises'
